doctype html
html
  head
    link(href='//maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootswatch/3.3.5/darkly/bootstrap.min.css', rel='stylesheet')
    meta(name="viewport",content="width=device-width,height=device-height,white-space:normal, initial-scale=1.0")
  body
    div.navbar.navbar-default
      div(style='text-align:center; color: #FFFFFF')
        h1 iErgo
    div.container
      div.jumbotron(style='text-align:center')
        h1(style='text-align:center')#header
          | RULA-Rapid Upper Limb Assessment
        div.panel.panel-info
              h2(style='text-align:center')
                | Purpose:
              panel-body
              h4 
                | To investigate the exposure to risk factors for upper limb disorders and provide a method of screening work population
                | quickly so the results that could go into
                | a wider, more versatile ergonomic assessment, while eliminating the need for assessment equipment.
        div.panel.panel-info
            h2(style='text-align:center')
              | Developed by:
            panel-body
            h4 
              | L. McAmney, E.N. Corlett
        div.panel.panel-info
            h2(style='text-align:center')
              | Developed When:
            panel-body
            h4 
              | 1992
        div.panel.panel-info
            h2(style='text-align:center')
              | Musculoskeletal Disorder Risk Factors Considered:
            panel-body
            h4 
              | Repetition, awkward/static postures, force, time worked without break.
        div.panel.panel-info
            h2(style='text-align:center')
              | Body Regions Considered:
            panel-body
            h4 
              | Upper arms, lower arms, wrists, trunk, neck, legs
        div.panel.panel-info
            h2(style='text-align:center')
              | Type of Jobs Appropriate For:
            panel-body
            h4 
              | Jobs with a range of frequencies, involving multiple body regions, standing or sitting or combination
        div.panel.panel-info
            h2(style='text-align:center')
              | Type of Jobs Not Appropriate For:
            panel-body
            h4 
              | None
        div.panel.panel-info
            h2(style='text-align:center')
              | Limitations:
            panel-body
            h4 
              | Some factors (e.g. twisting, lateral bending, abduction) are weighted equally no matter to what degree they exist (e.g. 5&deg;
              | twisting or 20&deg; of twisting)
        div.panel.panel-info
            h2(style='text-align:center')
              | Who is the Tool Design For:
            panel-body
            h4 
              | General Users
        div.panel.panel-info
            h2(style='text-align:center')
              | Minimal Amount of Training:
            panel-body
            h4 
              | 1 hour
        div.panel.panel-info
            h2(style='text-align:center')
              | Studies That Provide Evidence of Validation of the Tool:
            panel-body
            h4 
              | None found in literature
        div.panel.panel-info
            h2(style='text-align:center')
              | Electronic Version:
            panel-body
            h4 
              a(href='http://personal.health.usf.edu/tbernard/HollowHills/RULA.pdf') RULA.pdf
              br
              br
              a('http://ergo.human.cornell.edu/Pub/AHquest/CURULA.pdf') CURULA.pdf
              br
              br
              a('http://www.rula.co.uk/') http://www.rula.co.uk/
        div.panel.panel-info
            h2(style='text-align:center')
              | Reference of Peer-Reviewed Publication:
            panel-body
            h4 
              | McAamney, L., Corlett, E.N., RULA: a survey method for the investigation of work-related upper limb disorders
              br
              | Applied Ergonomics, 24(2), 91-99.
        div.panel.panel-info
            h2(style='text-align:center')
              | Industries and Jobs Where Tool Has Been Applied:
            panel-body
            h4 
              | Suitable for all industries
        div.panel.panel-info
            h2(style='text-align:center')
              | Is Tool Copyrighted:
            panel-body
            h4 
              | No
        div.panel.panel-info
            h2(style='text-align:center')
              | Instructional or Supplemental Information:
            panel-body
            h4 
              | None found in the literature
        div.panel.panel-info
            h2(style='text-align:center')
              | Equipment Needed to Use Tool:
            panel-body
            h4 
              | Worksheet, protractor, scale
        div.panel.panel-info
            h2(style='text-align:center')
              | Time Required Analyzing Typical Job:
            panel-body
            h4 
              | < 1 hour
        br
        p(style='text-align:left')
          a.btn-lg.btn-danger(href="/tool_definitions") Back

